body:
Anita needed fuel for the Forester. Since I wasn’t feeling that well still, she drove and I did the refuelling.

Anita ordered an Ice Cream from the McDonalds drive-through on the afterwards.

Katherine wanted to buy some things nearby, so I checked out the new Anaconda store. Spotlight moved out and Anaconda moved in. It felt weird to be in a new store that was still configured like the old store.
It was extremely hot and humid, so I scootered down to the creek to find somewhere in the shade with a breeze.
Walked to the Nurses Station with Kiara and Loren, but I don’t buy coffee there.
We dropped Katherine off at the convention centre where she is renting a graduation gown for the graduation ceremony later in the day
Since it’s a few hours until the graduation, we decided to walk over to the new Casino across the new bridge and go up to the observation level.
It was very hot and humid, so I bought an orange juice with ice at the bar on the observation deck level.

The big event - Katherine’s graduation with a Bachelors Degree in Games Design. We were seated on the left side of the stage, and the graduates were seated down on the main floor in front of the stage.
After the graduation and photography session, we headed over to Southbank and had lunch at the Japanese Restaurant.
I had to make an emergency trip to a toilet, so we stopped at the nearest shopping centre. I just made it really.
We’re doing another short walk this morning; this time starting from across the road and heading down to the coffee shop.
With all the rain there is no haze and it was possible to see the mountain range behind the mountains.
Coffee and a shared smashed avocado on sourdough toast with a fried egg and bacon extra.
There was a large number of stinkhorns near the crossing, but people have destroyed them.

We go to Bunnings and Anita was looking for a small stool to sit on when weeding. I wanted to see if they were selling Starlink equipment but didn’t see any. I will buy some more cameras for home next year. I would like to put one in the garage
Another rainy day. Fortunately it stopped for my walk to the bus stop.
Note as many people catching the bus this morning. The air conditioner leaks all over the seats, so not having many people is a good thing.
Last visit to see Erika at her nursing home. She didn’t talk at all; just smiled a few times and wasn’t eating much.
I rode into Brisbane to check out the new Kangaroo Point Bridge.
The local bakery was closed, so I didn’t have any lunch; only my thermos full of orange juice. I found an open Subways at QUT.
I rode back to the gardens and found a big shady tree to sit under. I had my camping chair and table with me.
The scooter has enough range to go to South Brisbane and back again twice, so I took a side trip to the picnic area at Toohey Forest.
Katherine thought I was going to be home today so wanted to go to Spotlight to buy some coloured thread. It wasn’t too late!
We took a different path through Nathan Heights back into the forest today.  It’s a very steep way so quite the workout for me.
A trip to Maccas
I didn’t want to spend Christmas Day sitting around at home, so we decided to go to Nudgee Beach for a short walk around the boardwalk there.
Dropped Katherine and Anita off at the bus stop. Anita was going to a job interview in the city on Boxing Day.

Picked up Katherine and Anita. Uniqlo called to say that they had already selected someone, so the job interview for Katherine was cancelled.

At least they were able to do a lot of shopping to make the trip to the city worthwhile.

I paid off the lay-by for the BYD Shark custom number plate. It should arrive towards the end of January. “A SHRK6”

I gave Anita the balance of the accommodation charges for our stay at O’Reilly’s Eco Lodges.

The OpenAI T-shirts have been in Brisbane a few days now and were transferred to a local courier. I’m worried they will arrive while we are away.
We ordered Subways for lunch as it’s the only local shop open.

We left late waiting for the garbage truck to pick up the Christmas rubbish. Anita said there were maggots in the bin. They never came so we headed off on our holiday.

The OpenAI T-shirts I ordered also arrived after we left. There’s nothing on the cameras, so hopefully they put the parcel in the letterbox.

We used the inland route to Canungra to avoid the huge traffic buildup on the M1.

I set up my travel router to repeat the Villa WiFi. The bandwidth is not great, so next time we stay here, I will bring the Starlink Mini.

Anita found a power point just outside the front door so I’m using it with the granny charger to recharge the Tesla back to 70%.
Order room service. My chicken was $45 and Anita and Katherine had roast beef and lamb for over $100.00.
We went for a morning walk along the pensioner track. There was a huge variety of birds active in the forest.
We then walked back to the cafe and had a coffee.
I was feeling tired after the walk and had a nap around midday for about an hour.
Katherine joined us for the walk up to the Cafe. They bought some things to eat for later and some souvenirs from the shop.
We stopped briefly at reception where I asked which coloured bins were for scraps and recyclables. The Red bin is for bottles and cans and the green bin is for the rest.
We walked along the boardwalk to the botanical garden and back. There were large groups on the same walk.

Walked along the pensioner track again this morning. I’m feeling a bit sore today and the walk up the road from the villas was difficult.

At the end of the Pensioner track we headed to the boardwalk, but this time we went clockwise along the border track and then back along the boardwalk. We encountered the birdwatching group where the bower birds nest is supposed to be, so we avoided them by going around.
We waited at the Stinson Memorial for the shop to open. The weather this morning was unexpectedly great. The sun was out, there was a cool breeze and the temperature was mild.

Dropped Katherine off at Daisy Hill. On the way back I drove past Redeemer College at Rochedale. It hit a pot hole near the Optus Satellite Station at the same time I discovered that the Tesla had a new corner assist feature.
Happy New Year 2025
